<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-147-996  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 147 996.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  April 1989 v38 n4 p603(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A near-optimal heuristic algorithm for single-row routing.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Liu, L. C.; Du, H. C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Single-row routing has been shown to be an intractable,NP-complete problem and conditions for obtaining an optimalrealization have been discussed.andP;  A number of heuristic algorithmshave been proposed but only one is based on a sufficient conditionof optimality.andP;  A tighter lower bound on the street congestion ofoptimal realizations is obtained and a heuristic algorithm basedon necessary and sufficient conditions of optimality proposed.andO;The algorithm can not be guaranteed to always generate optimalrealizations although it did produced them in 60 test instances.andO;The algorithm is shown to be time efficient as well.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Heuristic MethodsAlgorithmsNP-Complete ProblemsRouting.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   A given instance of 20 nets. (table)A sequence of net assignments. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>